canonical:
  title: 贈梓谷蘭若獨居僧
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 除聽松風耳不喧結茅深倚白雲根世人知路飜應恨石上莓苔汚屐痕
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 贈梓谷蘭若獨居僧
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 除聽松風耳不喧。結茅深倚白雲根。世人知路飜應恨。石上莓苔汚屐痕。
korean:
  title: 재곡난야에 홀로 있는 중에게
  author: 최치원
  language: kor
  text: |-
    솔바람소리 듣는 것 외에는 귀가 시끄럽지 않고
    띠풀로 집을 이으니 흰 구름 깊은 골짜기로다
    세상사람 예 오는 길 아는 것이 도리어 한이어라
    돌 위의 이끼를 신자국이 더럽히는구려
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0080&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: To a Solitary Monk at the Orchid Temple in Jagu Valley
  author: Choe Chiwon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Save for the whisper of pine wind, the ear knows no clamor—
    A grass-thatched hut nestles in the white cloud's deep embrace.
    Yet still men know the path here, and therein lies my lament:
    the moss upon the stone, once pure, bears now the stain of footprints.
  footnotes:
    - The poem presents an ironic tension between the monk's sought-after solitude and the intrusion of the outside world, with the final image of footprints on moss serving as a poignant symbol of how even sacred spaces cannot fully escape the world's touch.
